# Mini-program i18n

All user-visible text in the WeChat mini-program must go through `miniprogram/i18n/`. Do not hardcode copy in wxml, page js toasts/modals, tab labels, or navigation titles.

## Required pattern

1. Add keys to **all** locale files under `miniprogram/i18n/locales/` (`zh-Hans`, `zh-Hant`, `en`, `ja`, `ko`).
2. In wxml use `{{t.section.key}}` (page must set `t: getI18nData()` and refresh via `onLocaleChange`).
3. In js use `t("section.key")` for `wx.showToast` / `wx.showModal` / `wx.setNavigationBarTitle` / loading titles.
4. Tab bar labels use `t("tab.*")` in `custom-tab-bar`.

```xml
<!-- ❌ BAD -->
<view>点击登录</view>

<!-- ✅ GOOD -->
<view>{{t.profile.tapToLogin}}</view>
```

```js
// ❌ BAD
wx.showToast({ title: "已保存" });

// ✅ GOOD
wx.showToast({ title: t("common.saved") });
```

## New pages checklist

- [ ] Register nav title key in `nav.*` and call `wx.setNavigationBarTitle({ title: t("nav.xxx") })` in `applyI18n` / `onShow`
- [ ] Bind `t` + `onLocaleChange` (unsubscribe on `onUnload`)
- [ ] No literal Chinese/English/Japanese/Korean UI strings in wxml
- [ ] Every new string exists in all 5 locale packs

Language picker labels (`简体中文` / `繁体中文` / `English` / `日语` / `韩语`) stay fixed as product labels; do not translate those option names.
